<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	iCloud Key-Value Storage for cross-machine sync of friendly account
	names is wired up in FriendlyNameStore.swift but the entitlement
	below is commented out because the matching capability has not yet
	been enabled in App Store Connect for the
	com.strategicnerds.MailNotifierApp bundle identifier.

	To enable cross-Mac sync:
	  1. Sign in to https://developer.apple.com/account/resources/identifiers/
	  2. Open the com.strategicnerds.MailNotifierApp identifier
	  3. Toggle ON "iCloud" → "Include CloudKit support: NO" (KVS only)
	  4. Save, regenerate the provisioning profile
	  5. Uncomment the entitlement below
	  6. Bump build number, sign, and ship

	Local UserDefaults persistence in FriendlyNameStore continues to
	work today without any of this — KVS is purely the sync upgrade.

	<key>com.apple.developer.ubiquity-kvstore-identifier</key>
	<string>$(TeamIdentifierPrefix)$(CFBundleIdentifier)</string>
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
